soot.jimple.infoflow.data

Class AccessPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.infoflow.data.AccessPath
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class AccessPath
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    This class represents the taint, containing a base value and a list of fields (length is bounded by Infoflow.ACCESSPATHLENGTH)

      • emptyAccessPath

        private static final AccessPath emptyAccessPath
        The empty access path denotes a code region depending on a tainted conditional. If a function is called inside the region, there is no tainted value inside the callee, but there is taint - modeled by the empty access path.

      • getTaintSubFields

        public boolean getTaintSubFields()
        Gets whether sub-fields shall be tainted. If this access path is e.g. a.b.*, the result is true, whereas it is false for a.b.
        Returns:
        True if this access path includes all objects rechable through it, otherwise false

      • isCutOffApproximation

        public boolean isCutOffApproximation()
        Gets whether this access path has been (transitively) constructed from one which was cut off by the access path length limitation. If this is the case, this AP might not be precise.
        Returns:
        True if this access path was constructed from a cut-off one.
